Delegitimization 
This strategy of delegitimization by the 
producer of this text represents that a person, or 
group and/or idea is perceived as invalid. This 
strategy emphasizes only the group or its ideas 
that are correct or valid, while other groups and 
ideas are given emphasis that is not authentic or 
unworthy or invalid. In addition to being related 
to 
the 
subject 
or 
perpetrator, 
this 
delegitimization deals with valid or invalid 
statements. 
Delegitimization is a strategy of using text 
that considers the object of conversation not 
syah (canceling, considered not shah) or losing 
legitimacy in a certain context. Text producers 
revoke previously recognized status, trust, or 
authority. This process can occur in a variety of 
ways and can have a significant impact on the 
reputation and sustainability of the object of the 
conversation.  
 
 
