METHOD 
 
This 
study 
used 
qualitative 
research 
methods. Qualitative research is a method used 
to explore and understand the meaning that a 
number of individuals ascribe to social problems 
(Cresswell, 
2014). 
Qualitative 
research 
according to Moleong (2016) is research that 
intends to understand phenomena about what 
research subjects experience, such as behavior, 
perceptions, motivations, actions holistically by 
means of descriptions in the form of words and 
language, in a special, natural context. by 
utilizing various natural methods. Researchers 
use qualitative descriptive analytical methods 
which contain descriptions of facts and then 
analysis is carried out. The data used is in the 
form of words, images and not a collection of 
numbers. 
The data source in this research is the 
Independent Curriculum Indonesian Language 
Textbook 
published 
by 
the 
of 
Education, Culture, Research and Technology of 
the Republic of Indonesia. The data in this 
research are quotations in textbooks that show 
the values of peace to strengthen the research 
results. The data collection technique in this 
research is a library study technique. The library 
study technique is a data collection technique 
that uses written sources to obtain data (Meleong, 
2014). The data analysis method in this research 
is the content analysis method. The steps taken 
are, (1) reading the contents of the book, (2) 
looking for content that contains the value of 
peace, and (3) analyzing the contents of the 
content found. 
 
 
RESULTS AND DISCUSSION 
 
