Dara's mother said that Dara was expelled from 
school. In this case, we can see the impact of 
having sex outside of marriage that causes 
pregnancy, that is, its education is hampered 
because many schools choose to expel their 
pupils for fear of influencing or bad example to 
other students, besides the school does not want 
to bear the shame of the actions of one of its 
pupils. According to article 31 of the 1945 Basic 
Law, paragraph 1 states that ""every citizen has 
the right to education"". Then from that many 
schools are proposing to take the C package. 
In the 48th minute, Dara, Bima, and her 
parents came to the doctor to examine Dara's 
