Euphemism 
Euphemism relies heavily on the specific 
context and the audience's understanding to 
recognize the real intent behind the words. It is 
often used to soften harsh or unpleasant truths. 
The analysis addresses the usage of euphemism 
in Facebook posts that express verbal violence, 
with a specific focus on three occurrences where 
euphemistic 
language 
hides 
the 
inherent 
aggression and hatred. 
 
