Abstract: This study aims to explore the ecological content contained in Indonesian teaching 
materials in thematic textbooks for grade VI primary school students. The method used is content 
analysis. The data source in this study is Indonesian teaching materials contained in thematic 
textbooks intended for grade VI students. The textbooks analyzed were purposefully selected, 
namely textbooks published by the Ministry of Education and Culture (2018). Data were collected 
through a document study of the content of the textbooks, where each topic and subtopic related to 
ecology was identified and categorized based on the guidelines that had been prepared. The 
collected data were analyzed using qualitative descriptive analysis techniques. The process of data 
analysis involves the stages of coding data, categorizing data, and analyzing it to see the frequency 
of occurrence and distribution of ecological content in textbooks. The results showed that 
Indonesian teaching materials in thematic textbooks contain various aspects of ecology. The 
ecological aspects presented include types of plants and animals, the influence of geographical 
conditions on life, consumption of a healthy diet for the body, economic potential in terms of 
natural resources, the benefits of a healthy environment for the health of the body, and how to 
breed living things. The results of this study can be used as material for evaluating the feasibility 
of textbook content. 
 
Keywords: ecological, textbook, elementary school 
 
Ecological intelligence is one of the 
competencies that every individual must have. 
Ecological intelligence directs individuals to be 
wise in utilizing various sources of life (Todd & 
Gigerenzer, 2012). In education, efforts to create 
a generation of ecological intelligence must be 
carried out by all parties and by using various 
media. One very strategic learning media is a 
textbook. Textbooks are one of the primary 
media in carrying out learning (Rodriguez et al., 
2022). Apart from being a learning medium, 
textbooks can also be used as a medium for 
instilling and internalizing various life skills. 
Through reading, pictures and various learning 
interactions contained in ecological textbooks, 
can 
recognize, 
understand 
and

  
appreciate various positive things about life and 
the universe. Messages conveyed explicitly or 
implicitly can be an educational medium for 
students. 
Next, what ecological content is contained 
in the textbook? So far no data has been found 
regarding the diversity and ecological content 
contained in Indonesian language textbooks. 
Several studies related to study textbooks focus 
more on the quality or suitability of study 
textbooks in general. content or cultivation of 
ecological intelligence contained in lesson 
textbooks. For example, appropriateness in terms 
of content, language, systematics, graphics and 
other elementary aspects. Some of the research 
in question includes the readability of junior 
high school Indonesian language textbooks 
(Pujiastuti, 
2019), 
readability 
of 
text 
in 
Indonesian language textbooks for Class IX 
Middle School (Maghfirah et al., 2022), 
Analysis of the feasibility of Indonesian 
language textbooks for Class VIII junior high 
school students (Susilo & Mulawarman, 2022), 
and 21st-century Skills Indonesian language 
textbook for class X published by the Ministry 
of Education and Culture (Mhb & Mukhlis, 
2023). 
Outside Indonesia, research on ecology 
contained in textbooks has been carried out but 
has not yet explored the overall ecological 
coverage. These studies place more emphasis on 
ecology related to natural disasters. The research 
in question is: (Seddighi et al., 2021) entitled 
Representation of disasters in school textbooks 
for children with intellectual disabilities in Iran: 
A qualitative content analysis and (Seddighi et 
al., 2021) with the title Qualitative content 
analysis as a research method to investigate 
hazards information in school textbooks. What is 
interesting about this research is the role of 
textbooks 
as 
a 
medium 
for 
instilling 
understanding and awareness about ecology 
related to natural disasters among people with 
disabilities. In this way, people with disabilities, 
despite their various limitations, are still able to 
fight as hard as they can to try to save 
themselves when a natural disaster occurs. 
Likewise, for people who do not have 
disabilities, this research is very useful for 
providing knowledge and understanding about 
the appropriate attitude to provide treatment or 
assistance that suits the needs of people with 
disabilities when a natural disaster occurs. 
on 
textbooks 
in 
terms 
of 
ecological content is very important to carry out 
because data will be obtained regarding the level 
of commitment of textbook developers to 
participate in instilling ecological intelligence in 
students. The data obtained can also be used as 
evaluation material for the suitability and 
readiness of textbooks to participate in building 
a generation that has ecological intelligence. 
Findings regarding the level of ecological 
content can also be used as a basis for 
developing higher quality teaching materials, 
especially from the perspective of developing 
ecological intelligence. With the efforts and 
contribution of textbooks, lessons to participate 
in developing ecological intelligence for students 
can continue to be improved. 
 
METHOD 
 
This study uses a qualitative approach with 
a content analysis method that aims to conduct a 
comprehensive evaluation of the ecological 
content contained in textbooks. This method was 
chosen because it allows researchers to conduct 
an in-depth assessment of the ecological content 
contained in textbooks. This study focuses on the 
identification, classification, and analysis of 
content related to ecological concepts. 
The data source in this study is the 
Indonesian 
language 
teaching 
materials 
contained in thematic textbooks intended for 
grade VI elementary school students. The 
textbooks analyzed were selected purposively, 
namely textbooks published by the Ministry of 
Education and Culture (2018). The book was 
chosen because it is used on a national scale and 
is used as part of the teaching materials used to 
instill ecological education values from an early 
age. 
The main instrument in this study is a 
content analysis guide developed based on 
literature and ecological education standards. 
This guide includes key categories relevant to 
content, 
such 
as 
sustainability, 
biodiversity, 
climate 
change, 
and 
natural 
resource conservation. Data were collected 
through document studies of the contents of 
textbooks, where each topic and subtopic related 
to ecology was identified and categorized 
according to the guidelines that had been 
prepared.

 
 
The collected data were analyzed using 
qualitative descriptive analysis techniques. The 
analysis process begins with data coding, which 
is the process of identifying and labeling each 
unit of analysis that is relevant to the 
predetermined categories. Furthermore, the data 
were categorized and analyzed to see the 
frequency of occurrence and distribution of 
ecological content in the textbooks. The results 
of this analysis are then presented in descriptive 
form to provide a comprehensive picture of the 
ecological content in the analyzed textbooks. 
 
RESULTS AND DISCUSSION 
 
Research Results 
 
Based on research conducted on thematic 
books or textbooks intended for elementary 
school students in grade VI, data was obtained 
on 
various 
aspects 
of 
ecology, 
namely 
understanding plant diversity and reproduction, 
plant benefits, animal diversity and reproduction, 
animal benefits, places to live and worship, and 
being grateful for God's gifts in the form of plant 
and animal diversity. The following are findings 
of ecological aspect data contained in Indonesian 
language teaching materials in thematic books. 
 
Ecological Skills About Plants 
 
 
Picture 1. Ecological Skills About Plants 1 
 
The Picture (1) directs students to have 
ecological skills, namely by paying attention to 
plants in the neighborhood. Plants in the 
surrounding environment, in addition to adding 
beauty, can also provide oxygen, which is very 
beneficial for life. Therefore, paying attention to 
and maintaining the fertility of plants in the 
surrounding environment will make a very 
meaningful contribution to life. 
 
 
Picture 2. Ecological Skills About Plants 2 
 
The text fragment in the Picture  (2) informs 
about the diversity and beauty of plants. The text 
contains the instillation of ecological intelligence 
in students about how to care for and appreciate 
plants. 
 
 
Picture 3. Ecological Skills About Plants 3 
 
The Picture (3) informs about ecological 
intelligence in the form of instilling awareness 
for students that rice, tubers, vegetables, and 
fruits have many benefits for building energy 
and body health. The ecological skills instilled in 
students are in the form of awareness to be 
friendly and maintain soil fertility. Fertile soil 
will be able to produce a variety of fertile plants.

  
 
Picture 4. Ecological Skills About Plants 4 
 
The ecological skills contained in the 
Picture (4) are in the form of an understanding of 
how plants reproduce. This understanding will 
be able to direct students to be able to cultivate 
plants properly. Thus, students will be able to 
fight actively in increasing plant reproduction. 
 
Ecological Awareness About Animals 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
Picture 5.  Ecological Awareness About Animals 1 
 
The ecological skills contained in the 
Picture (5) are related to students' understanding 
of the benefits of fish for growth and health. The 
text also instills ecological intelligence in 
students about how to utilize the abundant 
natural resources in Indonesia. 
 
 
Picture 6. Ecological Awareness About Animals 2 
 
The text excerpt in Picture (6) instils 
ecological intelligence in students about the 
importance 
of 
understanding 
animal 
characteristics. This is important for students to 
understand so that they can participate in 
protecting animals from extinction. 
 
 
Picture 7. Ecological Awareness About Animals 3 
 
The text excerpt in Picture (7) instils 
ecological intelligence to students about the 
diversity of animals in Indonesia. This is 
important for students to understand so that they 
can play a role in preserving and protecting these 
various animals from extinction.

 
 
