Discussion 
 
A holistic learning approach, which aims to 
provide interest and motivation, is applied 
during hybrid learning in three study programs at 
Universitas Indraprasta PGRI. Every meeting, 
whether in class or virtually, is always given 
direction, 
inspiration, 
advice, 
and 
encouragement 
to 
according 
to 
validated 
instruments. 
Lecturers 
play 
an 
essential role as motivators. In particular, 
lecturers boost students' morale by advising

  
 
them to reduce playtime and providing support 
before they begin academic assignments. Using 
engaging teaching methods by lecturers can also 
inspire students and help them better understand 
the material being discussed. In addition to 
giving homework assignments, lecturers can also 
help students, provide a supportive learning 
atmosphere, and offer various assignments to 
students. 
The 
outbreak 
has 
changed 
everything in daily life, including education. 
With 
changing 
styles 
(Aldiyah, 2021) and learning effectiveness 
(Hidayah et al., 2020). The perception of 
distance learning in Portuguese universities 
(Gonçalves et al., 2020) results from these 
findings that students need face-to-face classes, 
which are very important for practical and 
laboratory classes. Perception and evaluation of 
distance learning in Austria (Bork-Hüffer et al., 
2021) The findings have significantly improved 
since the Covid-19 outbreak. Lecturers and 
students are adjusting to distance learning, but 
students are eager for a return to face-to-face and 
everyday life at the University. 
Until now, several universities in Indonesia 
have implemented hybrid learning, including 
Indraprastha PGRI University. Research has 
revealed that several difficulties must be 
considered when teaching hybrid (Gerbic, 2011). 
First, we must rethink pedagogy, which is the 
best way to learn hybrids between online and 
face-to-face learning. The need for online 
learning strategies is more significant than face-
to-face learning (Carvalho & Yeoman, 2021). 
Although there is a tendency to consider online 
learning as learning without the body, in practice, 
it is closely related to the physical environment 
in learning engagement (Gourlay et al., 2021), 
and face-to-face learning requires an emotional 
component in learning (Pischetola et al., 2021). 
Hybrid 
in 
universities 
is 
increasingly popular to improve post-pandemic 
teaching and learning (Raes et al., 2020). In 
hybrid learning, combining online and offline 
(face-to-face) learning, students engage with 
lecturers, peers, and materials in the classroom 
during 
face-to-face 
and 
online 
environments (López-Pérez et al., 2011). In 
hybrid learning in Indonesia, some students take 
classes online during the first week of classroom 
learning and the following week of online 
learning. 
In 
contrast, 
depending 
on 
the 
university's policy, others attend classes in 
person 
(Meydanlioglu 
& 
Arikan, 
2014). 
Lecturers and students have shown interest in 
using hybrid learning in higher education. 
Research conducted by Winata (2021) 
showed 
students' 
concentration 
and 
motivation levels during the Covid-19 pandemic 
revealed that they were only slightly motivated 
to study, and their concentration level in learning 
was relatively low. Research conducted by 
Cahyani et al. (2020) During the pandemic, 
online learning has experienced a decrease in 
learning motivation. Research by Loton et al., 
(2020) looking at student achievement and 
satisfaction during the pandemic found a 
decrease in student satisfaction with only a slight 
improvement in academic performance. A study 
by Mollenkopf et al. (2020) examined how 
Covid-19 affected student learning during the 
pandemic at a university in the Midwest of 
France. Moreover, Research by Boggiano et al., 
(2020) in various United Kingdom language 
institutions revealed that the epidemic has 
reduced the quality of online education. 
The application of hybrid learning interests 
and motivations provides significant evaluation 
results on learning outcomes. The findings show 
that the interest and motivation of hybrid 
learning have a strong influence on learning 
outcomes. 
The 
paradigm 
of 
emphasizing 
motivation affects students' ability to learn. 
 
CONCLUSIONS 
 
This study discusses the influence of 
interest and motivation in hybrid learning on 
Indonesian learning outcomes. Based on the 
results and discussion above, students' interest 
and motivation in hybrid learning affect 
Indonesian learning outcomes. 
It can be seen from the test of the 
significance of the regression coefficient that the 
regression coefficient is significant, which is 
indicated by the value of Sig = 0.000 and Fcal = 
19.682, while Ftable = 3.104 so that the value of 
Sig < 0.05 and Fcal > Ftabel or regression 
significance, which means that there is a 
significant influence of learning interest and 
hybrid learning motivation on Indonesian 
learning outcomes.","This study aims to determine the effect of interest and motivation in hybrid learning on the learning outcomes of Indonesian language courses. The method used in this research is quantitative. The population of this study were all students of Indraprasta PGRI University. The sampling technique used was simple random sampling. The number of samples in this study was 88. The hybrid learning interest and motivation instruments have been validated. Quantitative data analysis tested the significance of the regression coefficient and calculated the regression line equation. The results revealed that the application of hybrid learning interests and motivations had significant effects on learning outcomes. This finding can be seen from the results of the t test. It can be seen that the Sig value is 0.000 and Fhitung is 19.682, while Ftabel is 3.104, so the Sig value is < 0.05 and Fhitung > Ftabel, or regression significance. The paradigm of emphasizing motivation for students has an effect on students' ability to learn."
