Abstract: This study aims to describe the effectiveness of using padlet media in beginner-level 
BIPA learning. This type of research is experimental. The research sample for this study was 
BIPA students at Muria Kudus University, totaling 27 people. The data in this study are the results 
of BIPA learning using Padlet media. Data analysis techniques at this stage used descriptive and 
inferential statistical analysis. The results showed that Padlet media was effectively used in 
learning beginner-level BIPA at Muria Kudus University. Students' beginner-level BIPA learning 
outcomes improved by using Padlet media compared to before using the media. Padlet Media 
provides feedback, information exchange, and portfolio documentation for learning 
implementation. 
 
Keywords: Padlet media, BIPA learning, beginner level 
 
The BIPA programme stands for Indonesian 
for Foreign Speakers. This programme is one of 
Indonesia's diplomatic tools with other countries 
to introduce Indonesian language and culture. 
This is regulated in Law Number 24 of 2009 
concerning Flags, Languages and State Emblems, 
making Indonesian an international language. 
This legal foundation has gradually encouraged 
diplomacy efforts under the Ministry of 
Education and Culture. Language is one of the 
means or tools to communicate, despite having 
different cultural backgrounds (Noels et al., 
2020; Kim, 2020; Horwitz, 2020). 
The form of diplomacy in this research is 
through the Indonesian language. Indonesian is 
slowly being sought after by foreign countries, 
including Thailand, Vietnam, the Philippines, 
China, Japan, the Netherlands, and other foreign 
countries. The effort to introduce Indonesian to 
foreign learners is through learning Indonesian 
for Foreign Speakers (BIPA). In an effort to 
accommodate BIPA activities at UMK, the 
BIPA Unit (Indonesian for Foreign Speakers) 
was formed in 2019 with Decree No. 006/R. 
UMK/Kep/Sek/E.02.02/I/2019. The presence of 
the BIPA unit is expected to be able to 
accommodate the process of learning Indonesian 
for foreign speakers with the hope that the 
communication, knowledge, and skills of foreign 
students studying in Indonesia, especially at 
Muria Kudus University, can improve. 
The condition of BIPA learning at UMK is 
that there is no interactive media that supports 
BIPA learning. Previous research that has been 
done by researchers is the making of BIPA A 
textbooks based on Kudus local wisdom. With 
the research that has been done, the problem that 
is still found in BIPA learning at UMK is the

  
absence of learning media. Nugraheni & Riyanto  
(2022) explains the role of media in learning is 
veryimportant. This is because the media has the 
benefit of explaining or making someone 
understand a material. This statement is in line 
with the opinion of Mayer (2003) who explains 
that the selection of learning media is certainly 
not the same. Because, the determination of the 
media is certainly tailored to the needs of foreign 
students. 
One of the media that suits the needs of 
international students is Padlet Media. Padlet 
media is an online media that is able to convey 
ideas in the form of text, photos, and videos 
(Handini, 2020; Nozaki et al., 2023; Friska & 
Sembiring, 2021; Nugraheni & Salaebing, 2023). 
In simple terms, Padlet can be referred to as an 
online whiteboard that allows educators and 
students to convey and share ideas, concepts, 
and thoughts in the form of text, photos, or 
videos. According to Qulub, & Renhoat (2019), 
Padlet application is one of the internet-based 
learning media that functions as a place to share 
information in the form of text, photos, links, 
videos, and others, which are called walls. This 
application can be used by teachers as a 
substitute for the blackboard in the classroom. 
Padlet media can motivate students because 
it has the advantage of being a learning platform 
with free access. Padlet media can create a real 
classroom atmosphere because educators and 
students are at the same time. The existence of 
Padlet media helps teachers in presenting 
learning tools, teaching materials, attendance 
lists, and assessments directly in the Padlet 
column or using links from the web and Google 
forms that have been prepared previously 
(Detyna & Dommett, 2021; Afifah et al., 2021). 
Purba et al., (2024) stated that Padlet 
application has many advantages, including; (1) 
no need to download so it is memory friendly. (2) 
Padlet is able to create a real classroom 
atmosphere because teachers and learners are at 
the same time. (3) Everyone can convey ideas 
and concepts by using text, audio, or video. (4) 
Teachers can present learning tools, teaching 
materials, attendance list, and assessment 
directly on the Padlet column or use links from 
the web and google forms that have been 
prepared beforehand. In this case, Padlet 
provides complete link features. (5) Teachers 
can set up Padlet online whiteboard as attractive 
as possible and insert educational game 
applications such as Kahoot or Mentimeter. (6) 
Teachers can organise more varied learning 
activities based on individual, pair or group tasks 
or projects. (8) Teachers and learners can switch 
roles freely. (7) Class dynamics in the classroom 
can be recorded automatically which can be 
downloaded through share and export features. 
Furthermore, Budi (2022) also explained 
the advantages of Padlet, namely that it has a 
comment feature that can be used by educators 
to open discussion topics without having to 
worry about the topic being drowned out by 
student responses. In addition, Padlet also has 
more features that support face-to-face distance 
learning, such as customisable URL, YouTube 
videos linked to Padlet are free from YouTube 
adverts, and Padlet's link feature is very helpful 
as all uploaded files can be stored in the cloud. 
Based on these advantages, there are many 
benefits obtained from using Padlet media, 
including, first, Padlet media serves to improve 
learning outcomes (Nurhayati, 2022). Second, 
Padlet media serves to improve writing skills 
(Qulub & Renhoat, 2019; Lestari, 2018; Susanti 
& Ayuni, 2018). Third, Padlet media serves to 
increase learning activities, engagement, and 
student participation in the learning process 
(Gill-Simmen, 2021; Alghozi et al., 2021; 
Mobida et al., 2021; Novianto, 2024). Fourth, 
tablet media serves to foster students' interest in 
reading (Nurjannah, 2023). Fifth, padlet media 
serves to foster student self-confidence. Sixth, 
padlet media serves to foster student creativity 
(Reka & Mahmud, 2018). Seventh, padlet media 
serves to increase interaction and collaboration 
between students and teachers or with other 
students (Afifah et al., 2021; Jaya et al., 2022). 
Some of the advantages of padlet media can be 
concluded that this media is also suitable for use 
in language learning, especially beginner-level 
BIPA learning. 
The utilisation of padlet media in BIPA 
learning is to support the language skills of 
foreign students. Basically, language skills 
include listening, reading, writing, and speaking 
skills. Nugraheni (2022) states that language 
skills are a means used as communication to 
convey ideas, both orally and in writing. Aspects 
of language skills include listening, reading, 
writing, and speaking (Persky, 2019). In every 
learning activity, four language skills always 
appear, namely listening, speaking, reading, and 
writing (Saddhono, 2012). Relevant research in

 
 
this case is used as a foundation in this study. 
These studies include research by Bursan (2016), 
Hasanah (2018), Budiana (2019), Fahmi (2021), 
and Yuniatin (2022). The results of these studies 
have not used padlet media in beginner-level 
BIPA learning. Based on this, the novelty of this 
research is to find out the utilisation of padlet 
media in beginner-level BIPA learning. Thus, 
the main focus discussed in this study is to 
describe the utilisation of padlet media as a 
beginner-level BIPA learning media. 
 
METHOD 
 
The type of research used in this study is 
experimental research. In this study, researchers 
used a pre-experimental design model of one-
group pre-test and post-test design. In this 
design, a pre-test 
was conducted before 
treatment and a post-test after treatment. The 
experimental research in this study is a study 
that seeks to prove whether Padlet media is 
effectively used in learning beginner-level BIPA 
at Muria Kudus University. 
The population in this study was 27 
beginner-level BIPA students at Muria Kudus 
University, and the sampling used a total sample. 
So the number of samples used was 27 students. 
The data collection technique used was the BIPA 
learning outcomes test on the pre-test and post-
test.  
Based on the type of research used in this 
study, 
namely 
quantitative 
research, 
the 
researcher will process the data that has been 
collected using statistical procedures. The data 
analysis technique at this stage uses descriptive 
analysis techniques and inferential analysis 
techniques with the help of IBM SPSS 25 
software as a means or tool for processing 
pretest and posttest data. To test the hypothesis, 
the ANOVA statistic was used with the 
following test criteria for the hypothesis. The 
statistical hypotheses are: H : μ1 = μ0 H1: μ1 ≠ 
μ0 The testing criterion is that H is accepted if 
tcount ≤ ttable ≤ ttable and in H is rejected at 
the level of alpha = 0.05 and dk = n-1. 
 
RESULTS AND DISCUSSION 
 
Research Results 
 
The BIPA learning programme is an 
Indonesian language skills learning programme 
that includes speaking, writing, reading and 
listening for foreign learners. BIPA learners at 
the beginner level have minimal knowledge and 
insight and can be declared zero about the 
Indonesian language. Therefore, BIPA learning 
is designed according to the level or level of 
BIPA beginners. At the beginner level of BIPA 
learning, the Indonesian language content that 
must exist is teaching materials, learning 
materials, strategies, and learning methods. The 
materials taught in BIPA learning can fulfil the 
demands of knowledge that must be mastered 
and contain cultural aspects so as to facilitate 
BIPA learners in the process of learning and 
understanding Indonesian. Cultural aspects can 
be taught with the help of learning media. One 
of the learning media that can be used in BIPA 
learning is padlet media. Padlet media can be 
used to provide material or cultural insights in 
the form of various kinds of texts, such as 
descriptive texts or simple procedure texts. The 
following is an image of a media padlet 
containing descriptive text material. 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
