Discussion 
 
Padlet Media is effectively used in beginner 
level BIPA learning at Muria Kudus University. 
Based on the findings, Padlet Media is known to 
have 
many 
benefits 
including 
feedback, 
information 
exchange, 
and 
portfolio 
documentation. Firstly, Padlet media as a means 
of discussion. Padlet media used by beginner-
level BIPA learners at Universitas Muria Kudus 
functions as a means of group discussion.

  
Teachers and learners can paste the results of 
discussions or materials they have learnt on the 
wall. 
BIPA 
teachers 
can 
provide 
descriptive text material, then the teacher 
displays two pictures in it and students are asked 
to describe the two pictures using the Padlet 
application. Before the BIPA students submit 
their answers, the BIPA teacher asks each group 
to write down their group name so that the group 
that submits first can be detected. The group that 
submitted the answer first was considered the 
winner. So that BIPA students are enthusiastic 
and ambitious to be the first sender. The class 
will be more active and enthusiastic but still 
under control because students play with Padlet 
media. Padlet media is suitable to be used as a 
medium of collaboration between fellow BIPA 
learners. This is in line with the findings of 
Apriliana (2022) & Susanto et al., (2021) that 
Padlet can be a means to interact, share 
information, 
and 
make 
decisions/resolve 
problems. Furthermore, Rachmadyanti (2021) 
found 4 findings related to the advantages of 
Padlet, namely 33.3% of students liked Padlet 
because of the interaction with friends and 
lecturers; 30.8% found it easy to use Padlet; 17.8% 
helped students in understanding the material; 
and 17.8% attracted students' interest in learning. 
Second, Padlet Media as a means of 
feedback in learning. Padlet media can be a 
means to provide feedback to help BIPA 
students in understanding the lesson. Padlet can 
accommodate the responses from the students. 
This happens because this application is general 
and not individualised medisa. As such, it can 
replace the use of whiteboards to store 
information and allow the students to interact 
with each other and the teacher. Furthermore, 
Apriliana (2022) also stated that Padlet media 
can function as a means of feedback or giving 
responses between teachers and learners in 
discussing learning outcomes. 
Third, Padlet media as a means of 
exchanging information. Padlet media can be a 
means of exchanging information with fellow 
BIPA learners. Based on the findings, the BIPA 
learners really like Padlet because they can 
exchange 
information 
with 
other 
groups. 
Information that has been obtained by groups or 
individuals can be shared with other groups. 
Thus, the information conveyed by other groups 
or BIPA students becomes new knowledge. 
Furthermore, Apriliana's findings (2022) explain 
that Padlet media is very suitable to be used as a 
brainstorming tool. Brainstorming using Padlet 
is done by displaying the pictures attached to the 
Padlet wall, which aims to attract students' 
activeness in conveying ideas about sentences 
that match the pictures. This is very effective to 
increase students‘ creativity because Padlet 
provides adequate images and attracts students’ 
attention so that students have a high enthusiasm 
for creativity and sharing information with each 
other. 
Fourth, Padlet Media as a portfolio 
documentation tool. Based on the findings, 
Padlet media makes it easier to collect 
assignments. Padlet media is one of the new 
alternative media to document the results of the 
learning process in the classroom. In line with 
Jaya et al., (2022), Padlet works effectively in 
the classroom for activities such as exchanging 
ideas, discussing, and working on projects. (Budi, 
2022) also added that Padlet can be used by 
educators as a place to store student assignment 
files.  
Padlet media can be declared effective for 
use in BIPA learning at Muria Kudus University. 
This finding is in line with the results of 
Apriliana research (2022) that Padlet media is 
suitable for use if it meets the standards which 
include:  (1) Learning empowerment, where 
learners can play an active role in achieving, 
choosing, and being able to demonstrate 
competence 
in 
their 
learning 
goals 
by 
demonstrating the knowledge they have acquired.  
(2) Digital citizens, i.e. BIPA learners get the 
same rights, responsibilities, and opportunities to 
learn in a digital world that is interconnected and 
participate safely, legally, and ethically. (3) 
Knowledge constructor, where learners are able 
to 
critically 
process 
various 
sources 
of 
information with digital tools to develop 
knowledge, enhance creativity, and create 
meaningful learning experiences for themselves 
and others. (4) Innovative Designers, learners 
are able to utilise technology in the design 
process to analyse and solve problems by 
creating new, imaginative and useful solutions. 
(5) Computer-based Thinker, learners develop 
problem-solving 
strategies 
by 
using 
new 
technologies to test their solutions. (6) Creative 
Communicator, 
learners 
are 
able 
to 
communicate and express themselves creatively 
through digital platforms they master to achieve 
goals. (7) Collaborator, learners broaden their

 
 
perspectives and enrich their learning by 
working effectively with others in local and 
global teams. 
 
CONCLUSIONS 
 
The results showed that Padlet media was 
effectively used in learning beginner-level BIPA 
at Muria Kudus University. Students' beginner 
level BIPA learning outcomes improved by 
using Padlet media compared to before using the 
media. The frequency distribution of pretest 
scores shows that there are 10 students who have 
low scores in BIPA learning while as many as 17 
students or 63% have sufficient scores in 
understanding BIPA learning. 
Furthermore, the frequency distribution of 
posttest scores shows that there is an increase in 
scores after the posttest stage. Students using 
padlet media in BIPA learning there are 13 
students who have a score of 72-82 while as 
many as 14 students or have a high score of 83-
93 which means that student scores have 
increased after using padlet media in BIPA 
learning.  The results of hypothesis testing on 
pretest and posttest show a significance value of 
p=0.000 with a value of p<0.05 which indicates 
that there is a significant difference between the 
pretest and posttest groups. Based on the results 
of learning BIPA Muria Kudus University by 
using Padlet media, it can be stated that students' 
language skills in the posttest are better than 
before using Padlet media in the pretest. This is 
supported by the use of Padlet media which 
provides feedback, information exchange, and 
portfolio 
documentation 
for 
learning 
implementation.","This study aims to describe the effectiveness of using padlet media in beginner-level BIPA learning. This type of research is experimental. The research sample for this study was BIPA students at Muria Kudus University, totaling 27 people. The data in this study are the results of BIPA learning using Padlet media. Data analysis techniques at this stage used descriptive and inferential statistical analysis. The results showed that Padlet media was effectively used in learning beginner-level BIPA at Muria Kudus University. Students' beginner-level BIPA learning outcomes improved by using Padlet media compared to before using the media. Padlet Media provides feedback, information exchange, and portfolio documentation for learning implementation."
"DEVELOPMENT OF NATURAL DISASTER MITIGATION LITERACY 
TEACHING MATERIALS WITH THE HELP OF BOOK CREATOR 
FOR JUNIOR HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS  
Emasta Evayanti Simanjuntak, Vismaia S. Damaianti, Welly Nores Kartadireja, Nurfidah 
1,2,3,4 Universitas Pendidikan Indonesia 
1,2,3,4 Jl. Dr. Setiabudi No.229, Isola, Kec. Sukasari, Kota Bandung, Jawa Barat 
 
