reducing disaster risk. One of the efforts that can 
be 
made 
in 
is 
by 
implementing disaster literacy. Disaster literacy 
plays a crucial role in reducing disaster risk and

  
sustainable development (Logayah et al., 2022). 
Disaster literacy not only directly, but also 
indirectly impacts vulnerability to disasters, by 
increasing the capacity to anticipate, cope with, 
resist and recover from 
natural hazards 
(Hoffmann & Blecha, 2020). 
For this reason, students are expected to 
have a good understanding of the different types 
of natural disasters, their causes, impacts, and 
appropriate mitigation measures. A society that 
is aware and prepared for natural disasters can 
reduce 
losses, 
casualties 
and 
environmental damage. This requires high 
disaster education and awareness, especially 
among vulnerable populations such as students 
