the other hand, ideal conditions require students 
to have adequate knowledge and skills in 
disaster mitigation. Indonesia's geographical 
conditions require community preparedness for 
natural disasters from an early age. However, 
disaster mitigation literacy among junior high 
school students in Indonesia is still inadequate. 
Various studies highlight the importance of 
disaster education and awareness to improve 
preparedness and resilience. Disaster mitigation 
literacy is an important factor in reducing the 
impact of natural disasters by increasing 
community 
