devices such as computers, laptops, tablets, 
Android, and smartphones (Hanum & Amini, 
Book creator is a digital tool that allows 
users to create interactive electronic books 
easily. The platform offers a variety of features 
that allow the integration of text, audio images, 
videos, and other interactive elements, making 
the resulting books more engaging and dynamic. 
This book creator application has been widely 
known for its ease of use in developing e-books 
and e-modules so that it becomes a practical, 
effective, interactive, and efficient tool for 
learning (Hayati, 2023). The interactive and 
creative elements of the digital book creator 
media can make learning more meaningful and 
fun for students. In addition, the integration of 
book creators as digital modules can improve 
students' listening skills and make classroom 
activities more interesting (Muhisom et al., 
Study conducted by (Johnson, 2020)  
shows that the use of book creator can increase 
students' creativity and participation in learning. 
In addition, students also show a better 
understanding of the material taught through 
interactive 
digital 
books. 
Based 
on 
this 
exposure, it can be concluded that the use of 
digital technology such as book creators in the 
development of disaster mitigation literacy 
teaching materials is expected to bridge the gap 
between the current condition of disaster 
mitigation literacy and the expected ideal 
conditions.  
 
METHOD 
 
The research method used in this study is 
research and development (R&D) with a 4-D 
model. 
Thiagarajan 
(in 
Maydiantoro, 
2019) 
states 
that 
the 
4-D 
development model consists of define, design, 
develop, and disseminate. The 4-D model offers 
a systematic and structured approach to the 
development of teaching materials. With clear 
stages, instructional developers can focus on the 
necessary steps without spending time and 
money on unnecessary activities. However, this 
research was only conducted up to the 
development stage, namely define, design, and 
develop. 
The population in this study is all students 
of SMP Pasundan 3 Bandung City. Meanwhile, 
students in grade VIII A SMP Pasundan 3 
Bandung City became samples or test subjects of 
materials. The instruments used are in the form 
of non-tests, namely in the form of unstructured 
interviews with teachers and questionnaires to 
students and teachers. The interview was 
conducted to find out what kind of natural 
disaster mitigation teaching materials are in 
accordance with the needs of students and 
provide an overview of the development of 
materials assisted by book creators for junior 
high schools. Meanwhile, a questionnaire for 
students and teachers was carried out to better 
know the initial needs of students for natural 
disaster mitigation materials and book creators.   
Furthermore, the data analysis technique 
used in the needs analysis stage (define) is 
qualitative descriptive, namely by presenting the 
results 
of 
interviews, 
questionnaires, 
and 
literature reviews. At the development stage, 
quantitative descriptive is used. The expert 
validation 
instrument 
at 
this 
stage 
of 
development is in the form of a questionnaire 
with a list of statements using the Likert scale. 
Furthermore, 
the 
average 
results 
of 
the 
calculation of the validity level questionnaire 
were obtained with the following criteria 
(Lestari et al., 2018).

  
