In the next stage, earthquake mitigation 
practices or simulations are carried out in 
schools. After conducting tests and direct 
interviews, students practice mitigation when an 
earthquake occurs based on the material of the 
chapter ""Earthquakes"" read. To carry out this 
earthquake mitigation practice, researchers have 
provided earthquake audio and sirens for 
simulation. After listening to the instructions, the 
sound of the earthquake and sirens sounded and 
the students practiced the reading comprehension 
of the chapter ""Earthquakes"". As many as 75% 
of students can parakite mitigation when an 
earthquake disaster occurs. However, there are 
another 25% who are confused and only follow 
their friends. The reason students are confused 
when the simulation is carried out is that students 
forget the steps that must be done when an 
earthquake occurs. 
 
