In other words, homographs are related to 
spelling. This means that the spelling is the same, 
but the meaning is different. Homography lies in 
orthographic identification (writing and spelling), 
for example the word sedan (/e/ pronounced 
weak or pepet) which means ""little cry"" and the 
word sedan (/e/ pronounced bright) which means 
""a kind of passenger car""(A. Chaer, 2002; 
