Obligative Mode  
Obligative mode is a mode of speech that 
shows necessity and absolutes. According to 
Firman et al. (2016) obligative mode is used to 
express necessity by using the word 'harus', 
'haruslah' which indicates a prerequisite or 
something that must be done. The use of 
obligative mode in the expression of magical 
power on the walls of elementary schools is as 
follows. 
