Indirect Speech Act 
Indirect speech acts that occur when the 
speaker uses the speech mode not in accordance 
with the intent of the speech. Declarative 
sentences are used to inform something to 
partners, in utterances it is used to instruct 
(Wijana & Rohmadi, 2011:28). Indirect speech 
acts in the expression of magical power by using 
declarative-imperative mode. 
 
