The Third-Person Narrator 
Third-person narrators can be divided into two 
types, namely the omniscient third-person and the 
limited third-person. There are 18 Herman RN’s short 
stories that use an omniscient third-person narrator; 
no restricted third-person narrator was found. The 
third-person omniscient narrator is the narrator who 
can know all the activities of the character being told. 
 
In the short story “Makam = Tomb”, for 
example, the narrator is someone who is not a 
character in the story. The author uses a third-person 
narrator who is all-seeing, all-hearing, all-knowing. 
The following is an example of an excerpt from the 
short story. 
 
