The Function of Writing Javanese 
Javanese writings on outdoor media in the 
school environment have various functions. 
Room nameplate, for example, functions to 
provide room name information. Proverbs and 
expressions serve to advise about the teachings of 
character. Based on the results of data analysis, 
written Javanese in the school environment can be 
classified into four functions, namely (1) 
information, (2) advice, (3) appeals, and (4) 
greeting. The types of functions and their 
frequency distribution can be seen in Table 6. 
