The Javanese Local Wisdom Values 
In local wisdom, there is a philosophy of 
life, politeness, work ethic, mutual cooperation, 
tolerance, etc. The values of local wisdom are 
attached to the community which is obtained from

20   RETORIKA: Jurnal Bahasa, Sastra, dan Pengajarannya,  
 
experience in life (Rahyono, 2009). Character 
values that contain the teachings of character are 
taught in building student character in the school 
environment. Based on the results of the analysis, 
Written Javanese in the school environment in 
Yogyakarta contains the local wisdom values, 
namely (1) ethics and morals, (2) philosophy of 
life, (3) religion, (4) preserving the environment, 
(5) maintaining health, (6) tolerance, (7) work 
ethic, (8) cooperation, and (9) preserving 
Javanese script. The values of local wisdom and 
their frequency distribution can be seen in Table 
7. 
