and Ia (a name abbreviation from Sadia). These 
greeting types (to their biological mothers) were 
only applied for the 1980’s generation, whereas 
for the next generation (1990s and 2000s) they 
change the greeting to their mother with Mama or 
Ibu (mother in Indonesia language).  
 
