students responded by saying “Santet” (Doing 
witchcraft). This response invited laughter from 
the class because it was not the term that was 
usually used in the classroom interaction. The 
teacher also responded it with laughter. Laughter 
in this case is a kind of vocal characterizer created 
in the interaction. another example can be seen in 
the following extract: 
 
