think that’s enough for today. So .. ee .. see you for 
the next meeting”. It can be seen that during the 
time she produced the sentence, she was 
stammering “ee” as a signal of pausing. This 
extract shows a kind of vocal segregates as a part 
of paralanguage features. Another example can be 
seen in the following extract: 
 
