Teacher: “Besok lebih semangat lagi ya!” 
[Tomorrow, you have to be even 
more excited!] 
In the speech, the teacher conveys feelings 
of pleasure because he sees his students study 
seriously. The expression of pleasure is to foster 
enthusiasm and student motivation. Furthermore, 
in his speech, the teacher encourages students to 
be even more excited about learning.   
The teacher's speech showing appreciation 
and conditional statements can be seen in 
quotation 16.  
